{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:53:16.950Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing SecureLogin Component**\n\nI'm currently focused on the `SecureLogin.tsx` component, specifically the Identity Gateway screen. I need to ensure it supports the selection of all seven roles, including `client_admin`, `client_member`, `gff_admin`, and `gff_operator`. I need to ensure the logic and UI handle the list of roles correctly.\n\n\n**Designing Role Selection Screen**\n\nI've shifted focus to the visual design of the role selection screen. I envision a premium layout with either a left/right split or a grid of cards, each representing one of the seven roles. Clicking a role will trigger a visual selection with details. Below this, I plan to include a prominent warning about the frontend-only simulation, a call-to-action button, and a zero-trust handshake animation. Finally, it sets the preview session and navigates to the admin route.\n\n\n**Optimizing UI Layout**\n\nI'm now refining the layout of the role selector, aiming for clarity and visual appeal. I've mapped each role to a premium tag reflecting its clearance level, such as \"Client Admin\" (LEVEL III) or \"GFF Admin\" (LEVEL V). I'm also considering the implications for the code size in `SecureLogin.tsx`, and ensuring the file remains under 6000 characters for optimal editor performance. The goal is a highly optimized, stunning component.\n\n\n**Drafting SecureLogin Component**\n\nI've begun drafting the `SecureLogin.tsx` component in TypeScript, starting with the basic structure and imports. I've initialized state for `selectedRole`, `scanning`, and `scanStep`. I've defined a `rolesList` array, mapping each role to its label, clearance, icon, color, and description, which will drive the UI. This is the first version.\n\n\n**Defining Role Metadata**\n\nI'm now focusing on enriching role metadata to drive the UI further. I've defined descriptions for each role, alongside clearance levels and appropriate icons and colors. These are being incorporated into the `rolesList` array, providing the necessary data for a comprehensive and informative role selection experience.\n\n\n"}}
