{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:55:16.652Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Expanding Role Switcher**\n\nI'm thrilled with the initial refactoring; it's concise and functional! Now, I'm shifting focus to `components/private-app/role-switcher.tsx`. My current goal is to expand the role switcher, so that it can accommodate all seven roles, rather than just two.\n\n\n**Designing Role Selector**\n\nI'm now consumed with designing a beautiful dropdown selector for the expanded role switcher. The plan includes a button with role-specific color-coding and a chevron, leading to a popover dropdown listing the seven roles with a check icon for the active one. Selecting a role triggers a full-screen animation, sets the preview session in local storage, and fires a custom event. Finally, I'll run the original `onRoleChange` and redirect the user to the appropriate dashboard.\n\n\n**Refining Route Redirection**\n\nI've clarified the routing logic after a role switch! Depending on the selected role (client or admin), users now smoothly redirect to the appropriate dashboard: `/portal/dashboard` or `/admin/dashboard`. This elegance is thanks to the existing layout and route guard. Now, I'm checking the role-switcher component, aiming for a beautiful and clean implementation within the character limit, and reviewing icon options from `lucide-react` such as `Check`, `ChevronDown`, `Shield`, etc. I'll utilize Framer Motion to create smooth transitions.\n\n\n**Implementing RoleSwitcherPreview**\n\nI'm now diving into the `RoleSwitcherPreview` component implementation! My focus is on ensuring elegant hydration and handling `localStorage` access gracefully within a Next.js environment. I'm leveraging `useEffect` to manage the session state and provide a fallback during server-side rendering. I'm also importing several icons, and I'll use `useState` for the dropdown state. My goal is to craft a premium, compact component.\n\n\n**Developing Role Component**\n\nI'm deep in the code now, working on the `RoleSwitcher` component's core logic. I'm focusing on managing the active role state with `useState`, and handling the dropdown visibility using `setDropdownOpen`. I'm currently figuring out the effect that should hydrate the component when it first loads, and I'll use a `useEffect` to do this. I'm importing a list of icons, and I'll display an elegant list of roles! I'm also planning a smooth transition animation using Framer Motion. I'm also planning to utilize the `useState` hook.\n\n\n**Finalizing Role Options**\n\nI've just finalized the role options array, including ids, labels, clearances, icons, and colors. I've also implemented the `triggerSwitch` function that handles the role change: sets the dropdown, initiates a transition animation, manages `scanStep` state, and updates the active role and session.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:55:16.658Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"6bwaxipl","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/private-app/role-switcher.tsx","old_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState } from \"react\";\nimport { motion, AnimatePresence } from \"motion/react\";\nimport { RefreshCw, Check } from \"lucide-react\";\n\nexport function RoleSwitcherPreview({ \n  currentRole, \n  onRoleChange \n}: { \n  currentRole: \"Client\" | \"Administrator\";\n  onRoleChange: (role: \"Client\" | \"Administrator\") => void;\n}) {\n  const [switching, setSwitching] = useState(false);\n  const [scanStep, setScanStep] = useState(0);\n\n  const triggerSwitch = (role: \"Client\" | \"Administrator\") => {\n    if (role === currentRole) return;\n    setSwitching(true);\n    setScanStep(0);\n    const interval = setInterval(() => {\n      setScanStep(prev => {\n        if (prev < 3) return prev + 1;\n        return prev;\n      });\n    }, 350);\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      clearInterval(interval);\n      setSwitching(false);\n      onRoleChange(role);\n    }, 1400);\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"relative\">\n      <div className=\"inline-flex rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-black/40 p-0.5\">\n        <button \n          onClick={() => triggerSwitch(\"Client\")}\n          disabled={switching}\n          className={`px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-[10.5px] font-mono tracking-wider transition-all cursor-pointer ${currentRole === \"Client\" ? \"bg-white/10 text-white font-bold\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white/75\"}`}\n        >\n          CLIENT\n        </button>\n        <button \n          onClick={() => triggerSwitch(\"Administrator\")}\n          disabled={switching}\n          className={`px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-[10.5px] font-mono tracking-wider transition-all cursor-pointer ${currentRole === \"Administrator\" ? \"bg-white/10 text-white font-bold\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white/75\"}`}\n        >\n          ADMIN\n        </button>\n      </div>\n\n      <AnimatePresence>\n        {switching && (\n          <motion.div \n            initial={{ opacity: 0 }}\n            animate={{ opacity: 1 }}\n            exit={{ opacity: 0 }}\n            className=\"fixed inset-0 z-[100] flex items-center justify-center bg-black/80 backdrop-blur-md\"\n          >\n            <div className=\"w-80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#080808] text-center shadow-[0_0_50px_rgba(0,157,255,0.1)] relative overflow-hidden\">\n              <div className=\"absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#009DFF] via-purple-500 to-[#E4000F]\" />\n              <div className=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-full border border-white/10 bg-white/5 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4 text-[#009DFF] animate-spin\">\n                <RefreshCw className=\"w-5 h-5\" />\n              </div>\n              <h4 className=\"text-[14px] font-bold font-mono tracking-widest text-white uppercase\">RENEGOTIATING COMPLIANCE KEY</h4>\n              <p className=\"text-[11px] font-mono text-white/45 mt-2\">Isolating local thread stack and validating clearances...</p>\n              \n              <div className=\"mt-4 border border-white/5 rounded-lg p-2.5 bg-black/50 text-left font-mono text-[10px] space-y-1\">\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                  <Check className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-emerald-400\" />\n                  <span className={scanStep >= 0 ? \"text-emerald-400\" : \"text-white/30\"}>Resetting core local memory stack</span>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                  {scanStep >= 1 ? <Check className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-emerald-400\" /> : <div className=\"h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#009DFF] animate-ping mx-1\" />}\n                  <span className={scanStep >= 1 ? \"text-emerald-400\" : \"text-white/30\"}>Exchanging GFF_SHA256_PRIVATE_KEY</span>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                  {scanStep >= 2 ? <Check className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-emerald-400\" /> : <div className=\"h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#009DFF] mx-1\" />}\n                  <span className={scanStep >= 2 ? \"text-emerald-400\" : \"text-white/30\"}>Compiling role permissions</span>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </motion.div>\n        )}\n      </AnimatePresence>\n    </div>\n  );\n}","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { motion, AnimatePresence } from \"motion/react\";\nimport { RefreshCw, Check, ChevronDown, Shield, Cpu, Layers, Users, FileText, Eye, HelpCircle } from \"lucide-react\";\nimport { useRouter } from \"next/navigation\";\nimport { getPreviewSession, setPreviewSession, PreviewRole } from \"@/lib/preview-auth\";\n\nexport function RoleSwitcherPreview({ \n  currentRole, \n  onRoleChange \n}: { \n  currentRole: \"Client\" | \"Administrator\";\n  onRoleChange: (role: \"Client\" | \"Administrator\") => void;\n}) {\n  const router = useRouter();\n  const [activeRole, setActiveRole] = useState<PreviewRole>(\"client_admin\");\n  const [dropdownOpen, setDropdownOpen] = useState(false);\n  const [switching, setSwitching] = useState(false);\n  const [scanStep, setScanStep] = useState(0);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const session = getPreviewSession();\n    if (session) {\n      setActiveRole(session.role);\n    }\n  }, []);\n\n  const rolesList: { id: PreviewRole; label: string; clearance: string; icon: any; color: string }[] = [\n    { id: \"client_admin\", label: \"Client Admin\", clearance: \"L3\", icon: Users, color: \"text-cyan-400\" },\n    { id: \"client_member\", label: \"Client Member\", clearance: \"L2\", icon: Layers, color: \"text-slate-400\" },\n    { id: \"gff_admin\", label: \"GFF Admin\", clearance: \"L5\", icon: Shield, color: \"text-red-400\" },\n    { id: \"gff_operator\", label: \"GFF Operator\", clearance: \"L4\", icon: Cpu, color: \"text-purple-400\" },\n    { id: \"finance_admin\", label: \"Finance Admin\", clearance: \"L3\", icon: FileText, color: \"text-emerald-400\" },\n    { id: \"support_agent\", label: \"Support Agent\", clearance: \"L3\", icon: HelpCircle, color: \"text-orange-400\" },\n    { id: \"viewer\", label: \"Global Auditor\", clearance: \"L1\", icon: Eye, color: \"text-gray-400\" },\n  ];\n\n  const triggerSwitch = (role: PreviewRole) => {\n    if (role === activeRole) return;\n    setDropdownOpen(false);\n    setSwitching(true);\n    setScanStep(0);\n    \n    const interval = setInterval(() => {\n      setScanStep(prev => (prev < 3 ? prev + 1 : prev));\n    }, 200);\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      clearInterval(interval);\n      setSwitching(false);\n      setActiveRole(role);\n      setPreviewSession(role);\n      \n      const mappedOuter = (role === \"client_admin\" || role === \"client_member\") ? \"Client\" : \"Administrator\";\n      onRoleChange(mappedOuter);\n\n      if (role.startsWith(\"client_\")) {\n        router.push(\"/portal/dashboard\");\n      } else {\n        router.push(\"/admin/dashboard\");\n      }\n    }, 900);\n  };\n\n  const currentRoleObj = rolesList.find(r => r.id === activeRole) || rolesList[0];\n  const CurrentIcon = currentRoleObj.icon;\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"relative font-mono select-none\">\n      <button \n        onClick={() => setDropdownOpen(!dropdownOpen)}\n        disabled={switching}\n        className=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-black/40 text-[10.5px] hover:border-white/10 transition-all cursor-pointer text-white/80\"\n      >\n        <CurrentIcon className={`w-3.5 h-3.5 ${currentRoleObj.color}`} />\n        <span className=\"font-bold\">{currentRoleObj.label.toUpperCase()}</span>\n        <ChevronDown className=\"w-3 h-3 text-white/40 shrink-0\" />\n      </button>\n\n      <AnimatePresence>\n        {dropdownOpen && (\n          <>\n            <div className=\"fixed inset-0 z-40\" onClick={() => setDropdownOpen(false)} />\n            <motion.div \n              initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 5 }}\n              animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}\n              exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 5 }}\n              className=\"absolute right-0 top-full mt-2 z-50 w-56 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#0a0a0a] p-1.5 shadow-[0_10px_30px_rgba(0,0,0,0.8)] backdrop-blur-md\"\n            >\n              <div className=\"px-2 py-1 text-[8px] font-bold text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest border-b border-white/5 mb-1\">\n                Simulated Clearances\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"space-y-0.5\">\n                {rolesList.map((r) => {\n                  const RoleIcon = r.icon;\n                  const isSel = activeRole === r.id;\n                  return (\n                    <button\n                      key={r.id}\n                      onClick={() => triggerSwitch(r.id)}\n                      className={`w-full flex items-center justify-between px-2 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-left transition-colors cursor-pointer text-[10px] ${\n                        isSel ? \"bg-white/5 text-[#009DFF]\" : \"text-white/60 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/[0.02]\"\n                      }`}\n                    >\n                      <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2 truncate\">\n                        <RoleIcon className={`w-3.5 h-3.5 shrink-0 ${r.color}`} />\n                        <span className=\"font-bold truncate\">{r.label}</span>\n                      </div>\n                      <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1 shrink-0\">\n                        <span className=\"text-[7.5px] text-white/30 px-1 border border-white/10 rounded-sm font-normal\">{r.clearance}</span>\n                        {isSel && <Check className=\"w-3 h-3 text-[#009DFF]\" />}\n                      </div>\n                    </button>\n                  );\n                })}\n              </div>\n            </motion.div>\n          </>\n        )}\n      </AnimatePresence>\n\n      <AnimatePresence>\n        {switching && (\n          <motion.div \n            initial={{ opacity: 0 }}\n            animate={{ opacity: 1 }}\n            exit={{ opacity: 0 }}\n            className=\"fixed inset-0 z-[100] flex items-center justify-center bg-black/80 backdrop-blur-md\"\n          >\n            <div className=\"w-80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#080808] text-center shadow-[0_0_50px_rgba(0,157,255,0.1)] relative overflow-hidden\">\n              <div className=\"absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#009DFF] via-purple-500 to-[#E4000F]\" />\n              <div className=\"w-10 h-10 rounded-full border border-white/10 bg-white/5 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4 text-[#009DFF] animate-spin\">\n                <RefreshCw className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n              </div>\n              <h4 className=\"text-[12px] font-bold tracking-widest text-white uppercase\">RENEGOTIATING COMPLIANCE KEY</h4>\n              <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/45 mt-1.5\">Isolating local thread stack and validating clearances...</p>\n              \n              <div className=\"mt-4 border border-white/5 rounded-lg p-2.5 bg-black/50 text-left text-[9px] space-y-1 text-white/50\">\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                  <Check className=\"w-3 h-3 text-emerald-400\" />\n                  <span className={scanStep >= 0 ? \"text-emerald-400\" : \"\"}>Resetting browser memory stack</span>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                  {scanStep >= 1 ? <Check className=\"w-3 h-3 text-emerald-400\" /> : <div className=\"h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#009DFF] animate-ping mx-1\" />}\n                  <span className={scanStep >= 1 ? \"text-emerald-400\" : \"\"}>Exchanging GFF_SHA256_MOCK_KEY</span>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                  {scanStep >= 2 ? <Check className=\"w-3 h-3 text-emerald-400\" /> : <div className=\"h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#009DFF] mx-1\" />}\n                  <span className={scanStep >= 2 ? \"text-emerald-400\" : \"\"}>Compiling simulated RBAC permissions</span>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </motion.div>\n        )}\n      </AnimatePresence>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}}}
