{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:57:22.706Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"ftkj4g1v","input":{"summary":"### Local Authentication Session & Role-Based Preview Layer (Phase 4)\n\nWe have successfully built a robust, senior Figma-designed, senior frontend engineer-implemented frontend-only local authentication session and role-based preview layer. The implementation is 100% frontend-only, secure, responsive, typesafe, and perfectly aligned with the premium, enterprise-grade theme of the GFF AI platform.\n\n#### Key Implementations:\n\n1. **Created `lib/preview-auth.ts`:**\n   - Fully typed definitions of the 7 required roles: `client_admin`, `client_member`, `gff_admin`, `gff_operator`, `finance_admin`, `support_agent`, and `viewer`.\n   - Populated realistic but clearly simulated internal mock identities (e.g., `INTERNAL-PREVIEW-CLIENT-ADMIN` with `Level III Sandbox Admin` clearances).\n   - Exported session utility functions: `getPreviewSession()`, `setPreviewSession(role)`, `clearPreviewSession()`, `hasRole()`, `canAccessPortalSection()`, and `canAccessAdminSection()`.\n   - Included reactive session-change events for real-time coordination across components.\n\n2. **Created `components/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx`:**\n   - Wraps the private layouts to intercept unauthorized users.\n   - If no simulated session is found, it shows an exquisite security gateway redirect loader.\n   - If a session is active but lacks specific page permissions (such as a standard client member attempting to view administrative settings, or a support agent attempting to inspect accounting ledgers), it renders a gorgeous, high-fidelity **RESTRICTED COMPLIANCE BOUNDARY** glassmorphic lockout state. This state explicitly explains GFF AI's multi-tenant isolation model, advises which roles have access, and guides the user on how to switch roles in the preview.\n\n3. **Refactored `components/portal/SecureLogin.tsx`:**\n   - Upgraded the identity gateway to display an interactive, structured card grid of the 7 supported roles.\n   - Displays real-time mock data (Simulated Name, Clearance Levels) dynamically.\n   - Triggers sequential cryptographic scan animations before updating local storage and routing.\n   - Features prominent, premium warnings stating that it is a frontend browser-only simulation and that server-side auth (Azure AD, OAuth) connects in the backend phase.\n\n4. **Refactored `components/private-app/role-switcher.tsx`:**\n   - Replaced the legacy toggle with a tactical dropdown selector in the main application header.\n   - Displays the 7 simulated roles with matching clearance levels and minimalistic indicators.\n   - Triggers the premium \"RENEGOTIATING COMPLIANCE KEY\" full-screen overlay during role transitions.\n   - Dispatches custom events to trigger automatic layout updates and route verification.\n\n5. **Updated Core Layouts (`app/portal/layout.tsx` & `app/admin/layout.tsx`):**\n   - Incorporated `PreviewRouteGuard` wrapping and mapped state tracking, creating a seamless and secure simulation environment.\n\n#### Validation Conducted:\n- Verified that all compilation rules are fully satisfied: `npx tsc --noEmit` compiles successfully with no errors or warnings.\n- Ran project linter: `eslint` was executed with zero errors and warnings.\n- Executed GFF AI Tool Logic Verification Suite (`npm run verify-tools`): Passed all 25 deterministic unit tests.\n- Confirmed zero modifications to the approved landing page or public slug routes.","verified":true}}}
