ortal/SecureLogin.tsx`:**\n   - Upgraded the identity gateway to display an interactive, structured card grid of the 7 supported roles.\n   - Displays real-time mock data (Simulated Name, Clearance Levels) dynamically.\n   - Triggers sequential cryptographic scan animations before updating local storage and routing.\n   - Features prominent, premium warnings stating that it is a frontend browser-only simulation and that server-side auth (Azure AD, OAuth) connects in the backend phase.\n\n4. **Refactored `components/private-app/role-switcher.tsx`:**\n   - Replaced the legacy toggle with a tactical dropdown selector in the main application header.\n   - Displays the 7 simulated roles with matching clearance levels and minimalistic indicators.\n   - Triggers the premium \"RENEGOTIATING COMPLIANCE KEY\" full-screen overlay during role transitions.\n   - Dispatches custom events to trigger automatic layout updates and route verification.\n\n5. **Updated Core Layouts (`app/portal/layout.tsx` & `app/admin/layout.tsx`):**\n   - Incorporated `PreviewRouteGuard` wrapping and mapped state tracking, creating a seamless and secure simulation environment.\n\n#### Validation Conducted:\n- Verified that all compilation rules are fully satisfied: `npx tsc --noEmit` compiles successfully with no errors or warnings.\n- Ran project linter: `eslint` was executed with zero errors and warnings.\n- Executed GFF AI Tool Logic Verification Suite (`npm run verify-tools`): Passed all 25 deterministic unit tests.\n- Confirmed zero modifications to the approved landing page or public slug routes.","durationMs":3}}
